solution.p:
We raise both sides of the equation to the reciprocal power, \dfrac{4}{3}.
    \left[(2x + 1)^{3/4}\right]^{4/3} \amp= 27^{4/3} 
    \amp\amp  \blert{\text{Apply the third law of exponents.}}
        2x + 1 \amp = 81 \amp\amp \blert{\text{Solve as usual.}}
        x \amp = 40
